{"word":"H365 - אַיֶּלֶת - ʼayeleth - ah-yeh'-leth - Hind","slug":"H365","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אַיֶּלֶת</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼayeleth"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ah-yeh'-leth"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Hind"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>איּלת</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>'ayĕlĕth</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>ah-yeh'-leth</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p><ol><li>doe, deer, hind</li><li>\" Aijeleth Shahar\" is part of the title of <a href='B:230 22:1'>Ps. 22</a> and probably describes to the musician the melody to which the psalm was to be played</li></ol> <p />Origin: the same as <a href=\"#/H355\">H355</a> <p />TWOT entry: <a class=\"T\" href=\"S:0045 - 'wl\">45l</a> <p />Part(s) of speech: Noun Feminine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H193\">H193</a>, <a href=\"#/H195\">H195</a>, <a href=\"#/H197\">H197</a>, <a href=\"#/H198\">H198</a>, <a href=\"#/H352\">H352</a>, <a href=\"#/H354\">H354</a>, <a href=\"#/H355\">H355</a>, <a href=\"#/H356\">H356</a>, <a href=\"#/H357\">H357</a>, <a href=\"#/H359\">H359</a>, <a href=\"#/H361\">H361</a>, <a href=\"#/H362\">H362</a>, <a href=\"#/H364\">H364</a>, <a href=\"#/H424\">H424</a>, <a href=\"#/H425\">H425</a>, <a href=\"#/H436\">H436</a>, <a href=\"#/H440\">H440</a>"}]}